The Pillars of BBG Governance
To finalize this framework, we can summarize the BBG Protocol into four core tenets that represent the shift from the "Predatory" age to the "Pollinator" age:

Trusteeship (The Moral Core):
All infrastructure is Makkal Sotthu (Public Wealth). Managers are not owners; they are Trustees bound by a sacred, public oath to provide, not to hoard.

The "Bumblebee" Mandate (The Operational Core):
Robotics and AI are deployed as public services. They are the "bees" of the global ecosystem, performing essential tasks to keep the planet and our colonies thriving, with no motive to "take" or surveil.

Active Auditability (The Security Core):
Transparency is the default. Every robotic action is logged on an immutable, public ledger. Any citizen, anywhere, acts as an Active Auditor with the power to pause non-compliant activity and trigger a forensic review via the local "Robot Colony."

Reciprocity & Learning (The Evolutionary Core):
Mistakes are not hidden; they are "rehabilitated" in local colonies and analyzed. The data from these failures is shared globally, ensuring the next generation of "Bumblebees" is inherently more ethical and efficient than the last.

